          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/tree-pass.h\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/cfgexpand.cc\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/dse.cc\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/final.cc\"}\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/tree-pass.h\", \"symbol\": \"rtl_opt_pass\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/cfgexpand.cc\", \"symbol\": \"pass_expand\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/dse.cc\", \"symbol\": \"pass_rtl_dse1\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/final.cc\", \"symbol\": \"pass_final\"}\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/tree-pass.h\", \"symbol\": \"rtl_opt_pass\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/cfgexpand.cc\", \"symbol\": \"pass_expand\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/dse.cc\", \"symbol\": \"pass_rtl_dse1\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\", \"path\": \"gcc/final.cc\", \"symbol\": \"pass_final\"}\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The GCC RTL pass infrastructure is organized through a class hierarchy defined in gcc/tree-pass.h. The base class opt_pass provides the pass interface with methods for gate() and execute(). The rtl_opt_pass class (gcc/tree-pass.h:126) extends opt_pass specifically for RTL-level optimization passes.\\n\\nThe RTL pass chain begins with pass_expand (gcc/cfgexpand.cc:7010), which implements the conversion from GIMPLE-SSA intermediate representation to RTL. The pass_expand class inherits from rtl_opt_pass and is initialized with pass_data_expand which specifies RTL_PASS type and declares it requires GIMPLE properties and provides RTL properties (gcc/cfgexpand.cc:6994-7008).\\n\\nA representative RTL optimization pass is pass_rtl_dse1 (gcc/dse.cc:3784), a Dead Store Elimination optimization pass that inherits from rtl_opt_pass. It is initialized with pass_data_rtl_dse1 (gcc/dse.cc:3771-3782) and performs optimizations on RTL intermediate representation after the initial expand phase.\\n\\nThe pass chain terminates with pass_final (gcc/final.cc:4340), the final code generation pass that inherits from rtl_opt_pass. Initialized with pass_data_final (gcc/final.cc:4327-4338), this pass executes rest_of_handle_final() to generate target-specific assembly code from the RTL representation.\\n\\nThis chain represents the core RTL compilation pipeline: GIMPLE \u2192 RTL expansion \u2192 RTL optimizations \u2192 final assembly code generation. The rtl_opt_pass class provides the uniform interface for all RTL passes, allowing them to be composed into the optimization pass pipeline.\"\n}\n",
